// place-temple.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A PF2e temple / shrine. Institutional, not commercial: the framing
// is devotion, not trade. Gives a GM: the deity worshipped (PF2e
// pantheon), the temple's character, the head priest, the clergy and
// congregation, services offered (some with a suggested donation,
// some free), a worshipper present, and a hook.
//
// Entry table: [@TF-Temple]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues — same scheme as the shops):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// PF2e note: deities are drawn from the Core Rulebook pantheon. Each
// carries its real edicts/portfolio flavour so the temple's tone fits
// the god. Donation amounts are suggestions in COPPER (1 gp = 100 cp),
// not official PF2e prices — temples don't "sell" — marked (~).

Title: Temple
Use: people.ipt
Use: prices.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} temple
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Temple
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: deity=[@Deity]
Set: priest=[@PersonName]
Set: panc=[@Ancestry]
**[@TempleTitle]** *(temple in {$town})*\n&
**Dedicated to {$deity}** — [@DeityOf].\n&
**[@TempleCharacter]**\n&
**High priest:** {$priest}, a [@PersonDesc] {$panc} who is [@Personality].\n&
**The faithful:** [@Clergy]\n&
**Services offered:**\n&
[@ServiceList]\n&
**At prayer:** [@Worshipper]\n&
**{$priest} says:** "[@TempleQuote]"\n&
**Stirring beneath the incense:** [@TempleHook]

Table: TempleTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@TempleName][else]{$passedName}[end]

// If no name passed, build one from the deity + a temple-word. Always
// uses the actual {$deity} so the title can't contradict the
// dedication. (An epithet-based form was dropped because the epithet
// rolled independently and could name a different god than the one the
// temple is dedicated to.)
Table: TempleName
The [@TempleWord] of {$deity}
[@TempleWord] of {$deity}
{$deity}'s [@TempleWord]

Table: TempleWord
Temple
Shrine
Sanctuary
Chapel
Hall
House
Cathedral

// --- PF2e Core deities, each set with its matching portfolio. ---
// Set a deity AND its descriptor together so they always agree.
Table: Deity
{!deityOf=='justice, truth, and the rule of law'}Abadar
{!deityOf=='the sun, honesty, and redemption'}Sarenrae
{!deityOf=='nature, the hunt, and the wild'}Gozreh
{!deityOf=='valor, honor, and just warfare'}Iomedae
{!deityOf=='family, the harvest, and community'}Erastil
{!deityOf=='cities, wealth, and commerce'}Abadar
{!deityOf=='freedom, luck, and travel'}Desna
{!deityOf=='magic, invention, and the arcane'}Nethys
{!deityOf=='strength, battle, and the glory of war'}Gorum
{!deityOf=='the dead, fate, and the natural order'}Pharasma
{!deityOf=='love, beauty, and artistry'}Shelyn
{!deityOf=='secrets, ambition, and forbidden lore'}Norgorber

// Read back the flavour set above.
Table: DeityOf
{$deityOf}

Table: TempleCharacter
A grand temple of stone and stained glass, the town's spiritual heart
A modest neighbourhood chapel, well-loved and well-worn
A roadside shrine tended by a single devoted priest
An old temple whose congregation has dwindled to a faithful few
A newly raised hall, the paint and gilding still bright
A fortified temple that has clearly weathered hard times

// Clergy / congregation — uses the NPC generator for an acolyte.
Table: Clergy
[@ClergySize], led under the high priest by {!acolyte==[@PersonName]}{$acolyte}, a devoted acolyte

Table: ClergySize
a full chapter of priests and acolytes
a handful of clergy and a loyal congregation
just two priests and a rotating cast of volunteers
a silent order who speak only in ritual
a lively congregation that doubles as the town's social hub

// Services — some carry a suggested donation, some are freely given.
// Donations in copper, (~) suggestions only.
Table: ServiceList
- Blessing for travellers ..... freely given\n&
- Tending the sick ............ freely given\n&
- Suggested donation, candle .. (~) [@PricedAs with 5]\n&
- Suggested donation, ceremony  (~) [@PricedAs with 200]\n&
- Funeral rites ............... (~) [@PricedAs with 100]\n&
- [@SpecialService]

Table: SpecialService
Minor healing, by the priest's judgment and the god's grace .. freely given
Sanctuary offered to those in genuine need ................... freely given
Consecration of a weapon or tool ............................ (~) [@PricedAs with 300]
Reading of omens and fate ................................... (~) [@PricedAs with 50]
Holy water, blessed on the altar ............................ (~) [@PricedAs with 300]

Table: Worshipper
{!w==[@PersonName]}{!wanc==[@Ancestry]}{$w}, a [@PersonDesc] {$wanc}, [@WorshipperDoing]

Table: WorshipperDoing
kneeling in silent, intense prayer
lighting a candle with trembling hands
arguing quietly but heatedly with an acolyte
leaving an offering far too generous for their clothes
weeping at the foot of the altar
asking the priest a question they clearly fear the answer to
waiting, hooded, for the temple to empty
giving thanks loudly and at great length

Table: TempleQuote
The god's door is open to all. The donation box is merely... nearby.
We tend the sick and bury the dead. Coin changes neither.
Faith is free. Candles, regrettably, are not.
Speak your trouble. The god listens even when I cannot help.
Sanctuary is sacred here. Even your enemies know it.
Pray as you like, but do not pray for what you will not work for.
The dead are Pharasma's. The living are my concern.

Table: TempleHook
the high priest has not performed the dawn rite in three days
a relic has gone missing and the clergy are pretending otherwise
someone has been leaving threatening offerings on the altar
an acolyte whispers that the priest's recent sermons have turned strange
the crypt below has been sealed, and no one will say by whom
a pilgrim arrived gravely wounded and will speak only to the priest
the temple bells rang at midnight, though no one admits to ringing them
the god's statue is said to have wept; the priest forbids discussion

// Standalone temple name (sets a deity first).
Table: TF-TempleName
{!deity==[@Deity]}[@TempleName]
